A sensational move is the most talked-out event of the summer. The French football team in Ligue 1 is ready to break the world record of the settlements. The previous record was less than half that: it was born when Paul Pogba returned to Manchester United with a change of £89 million.
After the transfer, Neymar will become the world’s most expensive footballer and also the world’s best-paid professional athlete, as the PSG will provide him with more than £500,000 a week’s salary after tax.
Barcelona is known to be furious about the operation of the PSG and the way Neymar has been forced to leave the company. The source near Barcelona tells us that the company has been very well-involved with Neymar since he arrived in Santos in 2013.
Did the president of the PSG warn the football world about this move three years ago?
When Manchester City announced its interest in Blaise Mauitid in 2014, Nasser Al-Khelaif warned the best players in PSG.
"I'm not worried, because they know that if they're after our players, we'll be their opponent and we'll contact their players," said Al-Khelaif.
"We respect all clubs.
But if they're after our players, they'll have to face the consequences."
Barcelona seems to have been guilty of this: it expressed its interest in Marco Verratt, the middle field player of the PSG earlier this summer.
The PSG made it clear that it would not allow the Italian to leave under any circumstances. It may well be that Barcelona will lose its star player Neymar as a result.
